news.title: Rising prices, interest rates cool US home sales in April
news.para: Sales fell 2.4 percent compared to March to an annual rate of 5.61 million, seasonally adjusted, which was 5.9 percent lower than April 2021, the National Association of Realtors (NAR) reported.

news.title: China cuts key mortgage reference rate as Covid bites
news.para: "The five-year loan prime rate (LPR) is 4.45 percent," China's central bank said on Friday, lowering the rate -- on which many lenders base their mortgage rates -- from the previous 4.6 percent.

news.title: The Economic Times Real Estate Awards 2022-North rewards excellence in industry
news.para: The Economic Times Real Estate Conclave & Awards 2022 – North was graced by the presence of special guest Rajive Kumar, Chairman, Uttar Pradesh RERA.

news.title: USA: More buyers opt for adjustable-rate mortgages as rates rise
news.para: The increase coincides with a sharp rise in mortgage rates. The average weekly rate on a 30-year mortgage slipped this week to 5.25% from 5.3% last week, which was the highest level since 2009, according to mortgage buyer Freddie Mac. The average rate was 3% a year ago.

news.title: Haryana RERA issues notice to freeze accounts associated with Mahira Infratech
news.para: HARERA Chairman KK Khandelwal said, "We asked the bank to freeze the account of the company so that hard-earned money of innocent buyers can't be siphoned off to other purposes by the company.

news.title: SC upholds additional demand of YEIDA from allottees
news.para: ​​A bench comprising justices L Nageswara Rao and B R Gavai set aside the Allahabad High Court's verdict which had termed the Uttar Pradesh government's official order of 2014 as "unfair, unreasonable, arbitrary and in violation of the provisions of the Transfer of Property Act".

news.title: FIRs soon for soil dug from allotted plots in Greater Noida
news.para: The issue again cropped up during a recent meeting between Authority CEO Surendra Singh and some 42 allottees of industrial, institutional and commercial plots.

news.title: CBI files Rs 230-crore bank fraud case against Amrapali Leisure Valley Developers
news.para: In the forensic audit, it surfaced that the group allegedly diverted Rs 5,619 crore through different companies -- Amrapali Leisure Valley Developers Pvt Ltd, Amrapali Homes Projects Pvt Ltd, Ultra Home Constructions Pvt Ltd and Amrapali Grand, it said.

news.title: Chandigarh: Sanjay Colony residents go to HC, hearing on May 23
news.para: Submitting its reply, the UT administration stated that 21 days’ notice period was not expiring on May 22. The high court has adjourned the hearing for May 23.

news.title: To check mishaps, security to be upped at EWS flats lying vacant in Delhi
news.para: Four people, including a nine-year-old girl, were killed and two women injured after a four-storey vacant building collapsed near Bawana village in outer Delhi in February this year.

news.title: Karnataka: Gram panchayats can now sanction building plans
news.para: On Wednesday, the government also notified the Karnataka Municipalities (Amendment) Ordinance, 2002 after governor Thaawar Chand Gehlot gave his assent.

news.title: Brigade Enterprises sales bookings up 9% to record Rs 3,022 crore in FY22
news.para: Out of the total sales bookings, sales bookings in housing segment rose 11 per cent to Rs 2,950.5 crore during the last fiscal year from Rs 2,657.9 crore in 2020-21.

news.title: Manesar land scam: HC quashes ED chargesheet against two realtors
news.para: In June 2020, the ED had filed the second prosecution complaint (chargesheet) against them and 11 others in the Manesar land scam under the Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA).

news.title: Karnataka CM cancels BDA's land-conversion notification after public outrage
news.para: The Bangalore Development Authority’s notification issued for change of land use from ‘waterbody’ to ‘residential area’ in Doddabettahalli near Yelahanka by citing a cartographic error was on Thursday night spiked by chief minister Basavaraj Bommai, following public outcry.

news.title: Over 50% rise in property tax collection in Ahmedabad
news.para: As per Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation’s (AMC) statement, the tax department collected Rs 328.42 crore in property tax this year against Rs 218.17 crore in the same period last year.
